    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="650"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/379e</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        President of the Radio Corporation of America</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harbord</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>In view, however, of the special circumstances connected with the Mitsui station
                    at Peking, the Department renews the suggestion previously conveyed to you, that
                    you should exercise your option to <pb facs="0936" n="820" xml:id="pg_820"/>
                    decline traffic arrangements with that station until such time as the diplomatic
                    questions involved may have been so adjusted as to warrant the Department of
                    State in advising you that such arrangements may be put into effect without
                    detriment to American interests.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leland Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
